reviews.author: Baylor Knight
reviews.text: While this is a highly used platform, I don't understand why. It has a massive song library, but it sucks without the 15-20 dollar a month premium. I get ads every couple of song, I am locked to shuffle, I can't choose what song I want to listen to, and I only get 6 skips an hour but sometimes they don't refresh when they are supposed to. I don't like Spotify.

reviews.author: Adasaian Saundernian
reviews.text: I'm having a god awful experience with the app. I search up a song and it doesn't immediately play it? Why? Not only that, I literally have no control over my own playlist? Everything feels so restricted and unsatisfying. Listening to music helps me sleep and relax. For some reason, its a goddamn chore to do so.
